<br>
Zone- Bot<br>
Spell- 65 charm<br>
Buff- Burnout<br>
Mobs- Common elementals in bot, summon<br>
<br>
Now basically the mage uses his burnout to make summoned stuff in the bastion of thunder uber hasted and do uber dps. Parses of this on mage forums have been 500-600, and I've seen one do as much as 1100dps.<br>
<br>
Now hold on here for a second- with a focus item, Strike of solusek averages 2942.7dmg(20% dmg focus parsed, non crit) at 5.2 seconds with aa + 2.2 recast(check lucy) for 7.4 giving us on average 394 dps chain nuking. A mage charm for that results in, on average, 100 more dps than we can sustain. As the masters of fast damage, it seems a bit unbalanced that a mage can outdps our strongest nuke with one of these pets. Surely the mage dies when charm breaks, takes 96% rezz and chanter sets the mages back up rolling again no problem. I saw one of the level 66 lords in bot get killed in 32 seconds. It's also not very limited- they can use it to get specs, runes, and xp in a tier 3 zone and often solo like this... Duo or more I've seen for 14aaxp in a 10 hour period.<br>
<br>
Or maybe it's just the zone. After all, Bastion of Thunder does have the instant refresh on Harvest of Druzzil and Manaburn bug. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarelorn>Sarelorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/18/03 1:21:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm53.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=227.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mage dps with charm</span><hr size=1> Kind of curious that you'd single out mage charm here. You do realize that an enchanter can do the same thing, at less risk to themselves, and can also slow the mob they're killing? Not to mention they have a significantly larger chance of surviving a charm break. When their pet is almost dead, they can break charm, stun/root it, then kill it for even more xp.<br>
<br>
I've solo'd with Call a bit, and can tell you firsthand that 2 times out of 5 the charm breaks before I've managed to kill a single mob. When charm breaks, I'm paste.<br>
<br>
That said, I agree that it is overpowered. Lots of mages do. We never asked for a charm in the first place. You may notice on test that charm is being nerfed, so best bet is to wait and see what the final result is. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3284">Sarelorn Stonecaller</a><BR>
