<br>
Basically the charm style of mages was a suicide cycle there but 2 mages could take pets and just storm through mobs, taking them apart in seconds when it was working right... and produce that considerable aa as above. quadding hoha or pov was an aaxp an hour about thing.<br>
<br>
Surely it'd be nice to see mages in general solo at 65 with their pets- it's a considerable rarity compared to days of yore to see them using those guys solo(uncrowded server here, which is newer - kane bayle). Then again, consider that mage conj nukes at 65 are 91.6% of a wizard's evo ratio while at 44 are 82.9% as good... Seems as though lots of mage abilities were buffed for xping in comparison to wizards for groups(wizard quadding is less efficient mana wise at level 65 than it is at level 57). but then- having mage pets tank was made screwy.<br>
<br>
I suppose things look to be getting balanced. Charm xp uber while you can ! haste appears to be getting nerfed on pets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erun>Erun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/19/03 1:55:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm53.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=227.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizard Group Desirability</span><hr size=1> OK maybe I have no business posting here but...<br>
<br>
Im a level 60 mage, never been to BoT, can't charm anything....<br>
<br>
I will not challenge any of the DPS numbers of charmed elementals.  I cant prove or disprove them.<br>
<br>
However, even assuming that these numbers are true, it in no way affects Wizard group or raid desirability with respect to mages.<br>
<br>
We all know (yes Enchanters admit it) that charm is unbalanced and is in the process of being looked at.  Personally I would prefer that all this charm nonsense would be dealt with in a draconian fashion so that enchanters would be inclined to move back to their rightful place as a GROUPing class.<br>
<br>
When PoP was first released, Wizards had a legitimate beef against Mages inasmuch as Firebolt of Tallon was designated a vendor-sold spell and no similar wizard spell was so immediately obtainable.  Now that many months have passed and 61-62 spells are commonplace, and affordable for the most part, in the bazaar, the gripe that wizards have against mages is mostly nullified.<br>
<br>
I honor and respect my wizard cousins and cherish them as groupmates, and dearly hope that wizards will get beyond the perception that mages are a threat to their group desirability.<br>
<br>
